Ondo State Police Command said on Wednesday that the alleged rape case against a soldier attached to the 32 artillery Brigade, Akure is under investigation. It said it will leave no stone unturned to ensure that justice is done. A statement by spokesman Femi Joseph said there was no attempt to sweep the case under the carpet as being insinuated by some people. He said there was an attempt by some hoodlums to rob a commercial bank at iju on Tuesday at about 2 pm, adding that the intervention of “our men, who raced to the scene and engaged the hoodlums in a shootout, foiled the attempt.”